<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870224-0016 </DOCNO><HL> International Corporate Report:News Corp. Profit RoseBy 30% in Second Period</HL><DD> 02/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NWSEARNINGS (ERN)PUBLISHING (PUB)MOVIES, RECORDS, RECORDING STUDIOS (FLX)TELECOMMUNICATIONS, BROADCASTING, TELEPHONE, TELEGRAPH (TEL) </IN><TEXT>   Profit at NEWS CORP., Rupert Murdoch's world-wide media company, rose 30% in the second quarter ended Dec. 31.    Earnings were equivalent to $90.7 million, converting the Australian dollar at its current rate, up from $69.8 million a year earlier.    Excluding extraordinary items, the earnings increase was still 30%, with profit totaling $83.1 million. The company had extraordinary gains of $7.6 million during the 1986 period and $6.2 million a year earlier.    Sales for the quarter were about $866.2 million, up more than 36% from $634.8 million a year earlier.    The increases in sales and earnings came largely from including the results for Fox Film Corp. and Fox Television Stations Inc., which were acquired in December 1985 and March 1986, respectively.    For the six months ended Dec. 31, earnings rose 39%, to $126.4 million from $90.8 million a year earlier. Sales climbed more than 55%, to nearly $1.75 billion from $1.12 billion. </TEXT></DOC>